const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What does the AI actually reply to text messages?",
    answer: "The AI sends one professional text message that acknowledges the enquiry, confirms what the customer needs, and lets them know you'll be in touch. It's tailored to what they've written — if someone texts about a boiler service, the response references the boiler service specifically. It never sends a generic auto-reply. The tone is professional, friendly, and trade-aware."
  },
  {
    question: "Does the AI have a full text conversation?",
    answer: "No. SMS operates on a one-reply model — the AI sends a single, well-crafted response. This is deliberate. Text conversations can quickly become time-consuming and impractical. The AI captures the essential details in one exchange and leaves the detailed conversation for when you call the customer back."
  },
  {
    question: "How is this different from an auto-reply?",
    answer: "An auto-reply sends the same canned message to everyone regardless of what they've written. AI SMS actually reads the incoming message, understands the context, and writes a relevant response. If someone texts about an emergency leak, the response is different from someone asking about a routine service. The customer feels heard, not processed."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I still send texts from my phone normally?",
    answer: "Absolutely. The AI only responds to new incoming enquiries. If you're already texting with a customer about an existing job, you carry on as normal. The AI doesn't interfere with your ongoing conversations — it handles new leads so you don't have to drop what you're doing."
  },
  {
    question: "What types of tradesmen benefit most from AI SMS?",
    answer: "Any tradesman who gives out a mobile number benefits. Emergency trades like locksmiths and plumbers see a lot of after-hours texts. Tradesmen who advertise on classifieds and local directories get texted frequently by customers who found their number online. If customers can text you, you need something answering when you can't."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does AI SMS cost?",
    answer: "AI SMS is £19/month as either an add-on to the Core plan or a standalone channel. There's no per-message charge — unlimited incoming SMS messages are included in the price. The £299 one-time setup fee covers full configuration. No contracts, cancel anytime, 30-day money-back guarantee."
